The paper proposes a method for network representation that can handle heterogeneous information networks, which involves multiple types of nodes. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The focus on neural language modules and node classification also supports these potential sub-categories.
